{"tid":2137820,"cid":5,"subCid":11,"title":"[反了反了]抖音母公司將從北京搬到倫敦","createTime":"2020-08-03T08:14:47.000Z","updateTime":"2020-08-03T14:48:53.000Z","uid":123264,"like":299,"dislike":13,"uniUserReply":92,"replies":[{"pid":"71a2bd5df7fac9bd00393459dc420e56b30d8c00","tid":2137820,"uid":123264,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2020-08-03T08:14:47.000Z","msg":"<a href=\"https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-bytedance-britain-idUSKBN24Z0IE\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Farticle%2Fus-china-bytedance-britain-idUSKBN24Z0IE&d=Surr%2FXenqJySG8qcND35%2F%2BxpY9ERoCMedVnvBBvIoB8%3D&h=edc030be\" data-ef-url=\"https://embed.lih.kg/frame?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Farticle%2Fus-china-bytedance-britain-idUSKBN24Z0IE&h=526626ab\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.reuters.com/article/us-china-bytedance-britain-idUSKBN24Z0IE</a><br />\n<br />\nLONDON (Reuters) - TikTok owner ByteDance will move its headquarters to London from Beijing under a deal approved by British ministers, The Sun newspaper reported.<br />\n<br />\nByteDance&rsquo;s founders are to announce their intention to set up shop in London soon, the newspaper said, adding that the move was likely to upset U.S. President Donald Trump who has considered banning TikTok in the United States.<br />\n<br />\nIt was not immediately possible to reach TikTok for comment.<br />\n<br />\nMicrosoft Corp (MSFT.O) said on Sunday that it would continue discussions to acquire popular short-video app TikTok from Chinese internet giant ByteDance, and that it was aiming to conclude the negotiations by Sept. 15.<br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />阿侵一招令到強國公司逃出強國<br />\n希望咱們愛國的其他好同志不要效法啦<img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2/diu.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"5e9517d6dace3945c5c0d0cad16713605008adfb","tid":2137820,"uid":55384,"like":124,"dislike":4,"score":120,"citedBy":3,"replyTime":"2020-08-03T08:16:25.000Z","msg":"間諜中心<img src=\"/assets/